      "I.W. Publications (1958-1964) was part of I.W. Enterprises and named for the company's owner Israel Waldman. Reportedly Waldman came into possession of a printing company and among the assets were the production materials for several hundred comic books previously published by various publishers as well as a limited amount of previously unpublished material. Waldman equated possession of production materials as the right to reprint and I.W. became notable for publishing unauthorized reprints of other company's comics often with new covers as Waldman's windfall did not often include the production materials for covers. The later half of the company's existence it published comics under the Super Comics name. Usually these companies were out of business but not always.",NULL
